  "Notes": [
    {
      "Text": "Security update for tiff",
      "Title": "Topic",
      "Type": "Summary"
    },
    {
      "Text": "This update for tiff fixes the following issues:\n\n- Updated TIFFMergeFieldInfo() with read_count=write_count=0 for FIELD_IGNORE (bsc#1243503)\n- CVE-2025-8176: Fixed heap use-after-free in tools/tiffmedian.c (bsc#1247108)\n- CVE-2025-8177: Fixed possible buffer overflow in tools/thumbnail.c:setrow() \n  when processing malformed TIFF files (bsc#1247106)\n- Add -DCMAKE_POLICY_VERSION_MINIMUM=3.5 to fix FTBFS with cmake4\n- Add %check section\n- Remove Group: declarations, no longer used\n",
      "Title": "Details",
      "Type": "General"
    },
    {
